Method behavioural requirements:
- The integer array parameter `source` and `target` must not be null.
- The integer array parameter `source` and `target` must have the same length.
- The integer array parameter `allowedSwaps` must not be null.
- The integer array parameter `allowedSwaps` must have a length of 2.
- The integer array parameter `allowedSwaps` must have elements within the range of the length of the integer array parameter `source`.
- The integer result is the minimum Hamming distance between the integer array parameter `source` and `target` after performing any amount of swap operations specified in the integer array parameter `allowedSwaps`.